    "faq_YaXkAC": {
      "type": "page-faq-section",
      "blocks": {
        "question_RxjYDj": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "enable_keyboards": true,
            "enable_keycaps": false,
            "enable_switches": true,
            "enable_all_collection": false,
            "title": "What is a magnetic switch?",
            "text": "<p>Magnetic switches utilize the Hall Effect, actuating by sensing changes in magnetic flux. With no physical contact, they offer long lifespan and lightning-fast response.<br/></p>"
          }
        },
        "question_QiRWab": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "enable_keyboards": true,
            "enable_keycaps": false,
            "enable_switches": false,
            "enable_all_collection": false,
            "title": "Are your keyboards hot-swappable?",
            "text": "<p>Most of our mechanical keyboards feature hot-swappable PCBs, meaning you can easily change switches without soldering. However, please double-check the \"Specifications\" section on the specific product page to confirm.<br/></p>"
          }
        },
        "question_JanctP": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "enable_keyboards": false,
            "enable_keycaps": false,
            "enable_switches": false,
            "enable_all_collection": false,
            "title": "Linear vs. Tactile vs. Clicky?",
            "text": "<p>Linear: Smooth and quiet; Tactile: Noticeable bump for feedback; Clicky: Crisp \"click\" sound with a rhythmic feel.<br/><br/></p>"
          }
        },
        "question_7x7cnr": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "enable_keyboards": false,
            "enable_keycaps": false,
            "enable_switches": false,
            "enable_all_collection": false,
            "title": "Is it a Gasket Mount?",
            "text": "<p>It uses gaskets between the plate and case to eliminate hollow sounds, providing a bouncier feel and a \"thocky\" sound profile.<br/></p>"
          }
        },
        "question_qaGTEW": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "enable_keyboards": true,
            "enable_keycaps": false,
            "enable_switches": true,
            "enable_all_collection": false,
            "title": "Can I use standard mechanical switches?",
            "text": "<p>No. The PCB is designed for Hall Effect sensors and lacks pin sockets. They are only hot-swappable with other compatible magnetic switches.<br/></p>"
          }
        },
        "question_YfAYP8": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "enable_keyboards": true,
            "enable_keycaps": false,
            "enable_switches": false,
            "enable_all_collection": false,
            "title": "Does it have a warranty?",
            "text": "<p>We offer a 1-Year Limited Warranty covering PCB failures and non-man-made damage. See our Warranty Policy for details.</p>"
          }
        },
        "question_QFBVVC": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "enable_keyboards": true,
            "enable_keycaps": true,
            "enable_switches": false,
            "enable_all_collection": false,
            "title": "PBT vs. ABS keycaps?",
            "text": "<p>PBT is durable and resistant to wear, avoiding the \"greasy shine.\" ABS is smoother but tends to become shiny after prolonged use.<br/></p>"
          }
        },
        "question_6YxqEA": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "enable_keyboards": true,
            "enable_keycaps": true,
            "enable_switches": false,
            "enable_all_collection": false,
            "title": "What does \"Double-shot\" mean?",
            "text": "<p>The legends are molded using a second layer of plastic rather than printed. This guarantees the legends will never wear off or fade.</p>"
          }
        },
        "question_PNGQAp": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "enable_keyboards": true,
            "enable_keycaps": false,
            "enable_switches": false,
            "enable_all_collection": false,
            "title": "What is a CNC Aluminum case?",
            "text": "<p>Precision-milled from a solid aluminum block. It offers superior weight, stability, and a premium metallic aesthetic compared to plastic.</p>"
          }
        },
        "question_BRwPpy": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "enable_keyboards": true,
            "enable_keycaps": false,
            "enable_switches": false,
            "enable_all_collection": false,
            "title": "Does the PCB feature flex cuts?",
            "text": "<p>Yes, per-key flex cuts allow keystroke force to be distributed evenly, increasing the soft feel and reducing finger fatigue.</p>"
          }
        },
        "question_dWiMNR": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "enable_keyboards": true,
            "enable_keycaps": false,
            "enable_switches": true,
            "enable_all_collection": false,
            "title": "Do you support Rapid Trigger (RT)?",
            "text": "<p>Yes. RT allows keys to reset the instant they travel upwards and actuate the instant they travel downwards, perfect for games like Valorant.</p>"
          }
        },
        "question_TUWr8N": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "enable_keyboards": true,
            "enable_keycaps": false,
            "enable_switches": true,
            "enable_all_collection": false,
            "title": "What is the response latency of magnetic switches?",
            "text": "<p>Our magnetic keyboards feature ultra-low latency down to 0.125ms (1000Hz-8000Hz). They eliminate \"Debounce Delay\" for true instant actuation.<br/><br/></p>"
          }
        },
        "question_7mBfJb": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "enable_keyboards": true,
            "enable_keycaps": false,
            "enable_switches": true,
            "enable_all_collection": false,
            "title": "What does \"Hot-swappable\" mean?",
            "text": "<p>This means you can pull out and replace the switches directly without any soldering. This gives you freedom to mix and match different switches at any time.</p>"
          }
        },
        "question_pa9RCU": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "enable_keyboards": true,
            "enable_keycaps": false,
            "enable_switches": false,
            "enable_all_collection": false,
            "title": "Is this keyboard compatible with macOS and Windows?",
            "text": "<p>Fully compatible. There is a system toggle switch. We include replacement keycaps for both Windows and Mac to ensure your visual layout matches your OS perfectly.<br/></p>"
          }
        },
        "question_AJWbLY": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "enable_keyboards": true,
            "enable_keycaps": false,
            "enable_switches": false,
            "enable_all_collection": false,
            "title": "What connection modes does the keyboard support?",
            "text": "<p>Our keyboards typically support tri-mode connections: Wired (USB-C), Bluetooth 5.0, and 2.4GHz Wireless. You can pair multiple devices and switch seamlessly.</p>"
          }
        },
        "question_nM96Lg": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "enable_keyboards": true,
